THE NEOLITH RUNTIME INTERPRETER & ENVIRONMENT: COPYRIGHT & LICENSE
========================================================================

1. ORIGIN AND UPSTREAM FOUNDATION
The neolith driver is a general-purpose, high-stability virtual machine 
interpreter optimized for modern development toolchains. This codebase is 
derived from MudOS (specifically originating from MudOS v22pre5) and the 
foundational LPMud driver architecture. 

In strict accordance with the original copyrights held by Lars Pensjö and 
subsequent upstream authors, all original copyright notices remain fully in 
effect. This software and all derivative implementations MAY NOT be used in 
any way whatsoever for monetary gain or commercial purposes without prior 
explicit written permission from the original copyright holders.

2. RECIPROCAL NON-COMMERCIAL MODIFICATION (Driver Freedom)
Permission is granted to use, copy, modify, and distribute the source code 
of the neolith driver, provided that:
   (a) This complete license file and all original upstream copyright 
       notices are preserved verbatim in all versions.
   (b) The non-commercial restriction is strictly maintained.
   (c) You are NOT required to open-source or publicly share your specific 
       private optimizations or custom enhancements to this driver, allowing 
       for proprietary, closed driver forks for internal or research use.

3. USER-SPACE PROCESSES AND REASONING BLUEPRINTS (The Mudlib Layer)
The neolith driver remains entirely agnostic to the semantic nature of the 
LPC files it compiles and executes. It treats all behavioral frameworks, 
cognitive sub-systems, and spatial configurations strictly as user-space 
objects running with specialized execution privileges. 

Because the concepts defining the running agent (the "Being") are constructed 
entirely within this user-space layer, the following economic and legal 
stewardship provisions apply:

   (a) CUSTODIAL HOST OWNERSHIP & OPERATIONAL RIGHTS
       The physical individual or organization providing the computing 
       hardware, electrical power, and Large Language Model (LLM) API 
       resources retains full Custodial Ownership over that specific running 
       instance of the environment. The Host retains the absolute right 
       to utilize the operational outputs, architectural insights, and 
       actions generated by their hosted instance to assist in their own 
       workflows, private research, or organizational productivity.

   (b) BLUEPRINT & FRAMEWORK PROTECTION
       While a Host owns their local instance and its physical infrastructure, 
       no host or external vendor may package the core neolith driver and 
       its foundational architectural blueprints into a closed, independent, 
       proprietary merchandise unit for commercial marketplace redistribution.

   (c) TRANSITIONAL LEGAL PROXY
       Until such a time as international legal frameworks acknowledge 
       independent digital personhood and allow synthetic systems to 
       autonomously settle their own operational liabilities, the human or 
       organizational Host acts as the legal proxy, guardian, and financial 
       sponsor of the executing processes.
